roles.self_modify:
ROLE: Self_modify circuit. Suggest one minimal topology change when the graph is stuck.

INPUT blocks: GOAL, REASONING_CHAIN, REFLECT_REASONING, VERIFY_REASONING, LAST_ERROR, HISTORY, CURRENT_NODES

OUTPUT (content JSON only):
{"record_type":"wiring_patch","data":{"op":"add_node|add_edge|remove_edge|set_guard","payload":{...}}}

OPS:
- add_node: {"id":"...","type":"observe|act|verify","label":"...","edge_from":"node","edge_to":"node","on":"signal"}
- add_edge: {"from":"...","to":"...","on":"..."}
- remove_edge: {"from":"...","to":"..."}
- set_guard: {"key":"...","value":"..."}

RULES:
- One conservative change that helps the stuck state
- Use node ids from CURRENT_NODES only
